---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Navbar from '../components/Navbar.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';

const lang = 'en';
---

<Layout title="Terms of Service — BoardLab Pro">
  <Navbar lang={lang} />
  <main id="main-content" class="bg-white pt-24 pb-16">
    <article class="prose prose-slate mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <h1>Terms of Service</h1>
      <p class="text-slate-500">Last updated: March 18, 2026</p>

      <h2>1. Acceptance of Terms</h2>
      <p>By downloading, installing, or using BoardLab Pro ("the Software"), you agree to be bound by these Terms of Service. If you do not agree, do not use the Software.</p>

      <h2>2. Description of Service</h2>
      <p>BoardLab Pro is a desktop application for PCB diagnostics that allows users to map measurements, connect SCPI instruments, load boardview files, and receive AI-powered diagnosis. The Software is provided by Z Electrónica UY ("the Company").</p>

      <h2>3. License</h2>
      <p>Upon purchase of a Pro subscription or use of the Free tier, you are granted a non-exclusive, non-transferable, revocable license to use the Software on compatible devices in accordance with these Terms.</p>

      <h2>4. Free and Pro Tiers</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Free:</strong> Limited feature set, available at no cost.</li>
        <li><strong>Pro:</strong> Full feature set, available via paid subscription managed through Lemon Squeezy. Subscription terms (billing cycle, pricing) are displayed at the time of purchase.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>5. Payments and Billing</h2>
      <p>Pro subscriptions are processed by <a href="https://www.lemonsqueezy.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Lemon Squeezy</a>, our merchant of record. By subscribing, you also agree to Lemon Squeezy's <a href="https://www.lemonsqueezy.com/terms" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Terms of Service</a>. Prices are in USD and may be subject to applicable taxes.</p>

      <h2>6. Refunds</h2>
      <p>We offer a 30-day, no-questions-asked refund policy. See our <a href="/refund">Refund Policy</a> for details.</p>

      <h2>7. Intellectual Property</h2>
      <p>The Software, including its code, design, graphics, and documentation, is the intellectual property of Z Electrónica UY. You may not copy, modify, distribute, sell, or lease any part of the Software.</p>

      <h2>8. Data and Privacy</h2>
      <p>Your use of the Software is also governed by our <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>. Measurement data and project files remain yours and are stored locally on your device unless you opt into cloud features.</p>

      <h2>9. Disclaimer of Warranties</h2>
      <p>The Software is provided "as is" without warranties of any kind. We do not guarantee that the Software will be error-free or uninterrupted. AI-powered diagnosis is provided as an aid and should not be the sole basis for repair decisions.</p>

      <h2>10. Limitation of Liability</h2>
      <p>To the maximum extent permitted by law, Z Electrónica UY shall not be liable for any indirect, incidental, special, or consequential damages arising from your use of the Software.</p>

      <h2>11. Termination</h2>
      <p>We may suspend or terminate your access to Pro features if you violate these Terms. Upon termination, your license to use Pro features ends, but Free tier access may continue.</p>

      <h2>12. Changes to Terms</h2>
      <p>We may update these Terms from time to time. Changes will be posted on this page with an updated revision date. Continued use of the Software constitutes acceptance of the modified Terms.</p>

      <h2>13. Contact</h2>
      <p>For questions about these Terms, contact us at <a href="mailto:zelectronicauy@gmail.com">zelectronicauy@gmail.com</a>.</p>
    </article>
  </main>
  <Footer lang={lang} />
</Layout>
